"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The apply method in this context is being used incorrectly. The result of the apply method is a Series, and when assigning it to a new column, it should have the same length as the original DataFrame. However, the use of shift(-1) can lead to a mismatch in lengths, especially when the last element of each group is compared. This will raise a ValueError when trying to assign the result to df['z']. Instead, the logic should be adjusted to ensure that the output of the apply function matches the length of the original DataFrame.\", \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).explode().reset_index(drop=True)\"}"